729
00:45:31,721 --> 00:45:36,900
Guest: But yeah, so major in physics or astronomy and then go to graduate school.

730
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:45,020
Guest: I mean, if you want to make research contributions to the field, it's very, very difficult to do that without a PhD.

731
00:45:45,661 --> 00:45:51,680
Guest: If you want to make contributions to observational astronomy, that you can do without a PhD.

732
00:45:52,121 --> 00:45:59,180
Guest: You just need to get a really good telescope and become very familiar with the night sky and you could easily discover an asteroid or a comet or something like that.

733
00:45:59,481 --> 00:46:07,460
Guest: But if you want to make research contributions to our theories of how the universe works and where it came from, you kind of need to get a PhD.

734
00:46:09,302 --> 00:46:12,420
